ERROR:

Handling exception class java.lang.ClassCastException: class com.jss.core.enums.OrderTypeEnum cannot be cast to class de.hybris.platform.core.model.ItemModel (com.jss.core.enums.OrderTypeEnum and de.hybris.platform.core.model.ItemModel are in unnamed module of loader de.hybris.tomcat.HybrisWebappLoader$HybrisWebappClassLoader$1$1 @21cf4dd4)

CASE:
New enum created in items.xml and added the attributes in order model to set the type of an order:
<enumtype generate="true" code="OrderTypeEnum" autocreate="true" dynamic="true">
   <value code="SalesOrder"/>
   <value code="CustomerOrder"/>
   <value code="S4HanaOrder"/>
</enumtype>

Attribute create with part of to true to create a new type of OrderTypeEnum if it is not found in the system to avoid the error:
<attribute autocreate="true" qualifier="orderType" type="OrderTypeEnum" generate="true">
   <persistence type="property"/>
   <modifiers read="true" write="true" search="true" optional="true" partof="true"/>
</attribute>

Explanation:
  partof="true" means the attribute declares a composition relationship implying the referenced item lifecycle depends on the owning item (like a child entity).
  This relationship is only valid for references to other ItemModel instances, but enums are not ItemModelsâ€”they are enumeration values.
  So when the platform tries to treat your enum attribute as a child item (due to partof="true"), it attempts to cast the enum value to ItemModel which fails causing the ClassCastException.

FIX:
  Remove partof="true" from the enum attribute definition. Enums must not be marked as partof because they are value types, not separate items.
  corrected attribute should be:
      <attribute autocreate="true" qualifier="orderType" type="OrderTypeEnum" generate="true">
         <persistence type="property"/>
         <modifiers read="true" write="true" search="true" optional="true"/>
      </attribute>


  
